Following his discharge from hospital over Covid-19, President Muhammadu Buhari, Wednesday wrote to Boris Johnson, British Prime Minister, congratulating him for his quick recovery. In a congratulatory letter dated April 14, 2020 to Mr Johnson, Buhari said he received “with great relief the news of your discharge from hospital after being successfully treated for Covid-19.” Expressing delight on behalf of his family and the government and people of Nigeria, at the Prime Minister’s recovery, the Nigerian leader according to Femi Adesina said; “We all join you in appreciating the wonderful staff at both the hospital and the NHS who worked round the clock to look after you and those afflicted by Covid-19.” President Buhari also wished the Prime Minister “full recovery and good health in the coming days.” Vanguard By Johnbosco Agbakwuru ABUJA--—-PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has sent a solidarity message to the British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson who was reportedly taken to Intensive Care Unit, ICU, as a result of COVID-19 (Coronavirus) pandemic. President Buhari in the solidarity message prayed that Prime Minister Johnson should get well soon. This… April 7, 2020 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday sent a message of solidarity to the British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson, who has been hospitalised over “persistent symptoms” of coronavirus and wished him a quick recovery and restoration to full health. The President’s solidarity message was conveyed via a statement issued by his Senior… April 7, 2020 In "News" *Global infection passes 1.4m *US records 1.150 deaths in 24hrs *World leaders wish UK PM quick recovery By Henry Ojelu, with agency report A coronavirus treatment already approved in the UK and US which uses blood from recovered patients can help the infected get better within three days, a study… April 8, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"